
// The code snippet demonstrates the use of the [sockets.signal] slot to send a message to a specific session. It constructs the message content using the [strings.concat] slot and specifies the message type as "system". The [sockets.signal] slot targets a session ID retrieved from the [.arguments] node, and the [args] node contains the message details to be transmitted.
sockets.signal:x:@.arguments/*/session
   args
      message:x:@strings.concat
      type:system
